# {{.WorkspaceName}} Workspace Development Skill

The root skill handles workspace-level routing, cross-project coordination, and impact radius. Child project implementation details, coding style, business methods, and project rules must be read from the corresponding child skill and `references/project-spec.md`.

## Workflow

1. Classify the task scope by path: single child project, contracts, shared code, infra, or cross-project flow.
2. Read [Workspace Overview](./references/workspace-overview.md) and [Cross-Project Rules](./references/cross-project-rules.md).
3. Load affected child project `SKILL.md` files, then load each child project's `references/project-spec.md` as needed.
4. For cross-project work, settle the contract or shared interface before splitting implementation boundaries.
5. Do not promote one child project's internal convention into a workspace rule; child details belong to child skills.

## Routing Rules

{{range .Projects}}
- `{{.Path}}/**` -> read `{{.Path}}/.agents/skills/{{.SkillName}}/SKILL.md` or `{{.Path}}/.claude/skills/{{.SkillName}}/SKILL.md`, then read `{{.Path}}/.agents/skills/{{.SkillName}}/references/project-spec.md` as needed
{{end}}
{{if .Contracts}}
- When contract paths change, read producer and consumer child project skills together; do not update only one side.
{{end}}
{{if .Shared}}
- When shared paths change, read every child project skill that imports, packages, or generates the shared content.
{{end}}
{{if .Infra}}
- When infra paths change, read child project skills affected by deployment, config, gateway, or middleware rules.
{{end}}

