## Parallel Work

- Distinct child project paths may be handled by multiple agents in parallel when each agent writes only within its child project.
- The same file or path under `contracts`, `shared`, or `infra` should be handled serially; stabilize the contract or shared interface before child projects proceed in parallel.
- Before parallel work, list affected projects and write boundaries. After parallel work, verify interface, generated artifacts, config, and tests stay consistent.
